The paper presents a novel algorithm for reducing a symmetric matrix to a triangular factorization which reveals the rank profile matrix. This involves numerical linear algebra techniques and matrix factorization, which are typically covered in the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of pivoting strategies and the shape of the block diagonal, which are relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Finally, the experimental results and comparison with state-of-the-art methods suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
